        p Hi, I’m Oliver. (White shirt, standing, in the picture.)

        p I'm a programmer, manager, juggler, husband, and father of two.

        p.
          I've worked at
          <a href="http://apple.com">Apple</a> (consumer electronics and computers),
          <a href="https://nest.com">Nest Labs</a> (wifi-connected learning thermostats),
          AOL (during the reboot; not as stodgy &ndash; briefly &ndash; as it sounds),
          and a bunch of start-ups.

        p.
          I'm based in Amherst, Massachusetts, but I’ve spent most of my life commuting to Boston
          and/or telecommuting to California.

        p.
          If you want to get in touch with me, <a href="mailto:steele@osteele.com">email</a> is best.
          If you’re a recruiter, try to find someone who knows me or who I’ll recognize from their name or work;
          and ask for an introduction.

        p.
          I'm also on <a href="http://github.com/osteele">GitHub</a>,
          <a href="https://twitter.com/osteele">Twitter</a>,
          and <a href="http://www.linkedin.com/in/osteele">LinkedIn</a>.

      section#code
        h2 Code
        p I consider coding (like writing) as a way to think.
        p.
          I prefer to work with people who code in order to clarify how to talk, as often as they talk in order to clarify how to code.
          (That is, neither exclusively, and neither with fear.)
        p. Good code is beautiful.
        p.
          I currently work mostly in Ruby, Python, JavaScript &amp; CoffeeScript;
          previously in C, C++, Common Lisp, Java, SmallTalk, assembly, and (of course) Dylan;
          and smaller projects in Haskell and bash.
          For server work I've used mostly Rails, Django, Sinatra, and Express; MySQL, Postgres, and Redis;
          Apache and nginx; and AWS (and previously DreamHost, SliceHost and colos).
        p.
          <a href="http://code.osteele.com">GitHub code page</a> lists a few of my current side projects.
          This year these are mostly around music theory and notation.
        p.
          My complete GitHub repository list is <a href="http://github.com/osteele">here</a>.

        h4 Historical Code
        ul
          li.
            Pre-GitHub <a href="/sources">sources page</a>.
