            of <code>canvas</code> and <code>fillText</code> to HTML,
            and of the web developer console to modern web browsers,
            made a number of these unnecessary.
          li <a href="/projects/pywordnet/">PyWordNet</a> was folded into <a href="http://nltk.org/">NLTK</a>.
          li.
            These days I use <a href="http://underscorejs.org">Underscore</a>
            and <a href="http://coffeescript.org">CoffeeScript</a>
            instead of my own older <a href="/projects/pywordnet/">Functional JavaScript</a>
            and <a href="https://github.com/osteele/collections-js">Collections.js</a>.

